<section id="fs-id1169597682368">
<title>Find the <emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis>- and <emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis>- Intercepts from an Equation of a Line</title>
<para id="fs-id1169597824362">Recognizing that the <term class="no-emphasis"><emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis>- intercept</term> occurs when <emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis> is zero and that the <emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis>- intercept occurs when <emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis> is zero, gives us a method to find the intercepts of a line from its equation. To find the <emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis>- intercept, let <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> and solve for <emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis>. To find the <term class="no-emphasis"><emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis>- intercept</term>, let <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> and solve for <emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis>.</para>
<note id="fs-id1169597692471">
<title>Find the <emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis>- and <emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis>- Intercepts from the Equation of a Line</title>
<para id="fs-id1169597536561">Use the equation of the line. To find:</para>
<list id="fs-id1169597804239" list-type="bulleted" bullet-style="bullet">
<item>the <emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis>- intercept of the line, let <m:math>
<m:mrow>
<m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow>
</m:math> and solve for <m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:math>.</item>
<item>the <emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis>- intercept of the line, let <m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:math> and solve for <m:math><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:math>.</item>
</list>
</note>
<para id="fs-id1171789604649"> </para>
<example id="fs-id1169595229245">
<exercise id="fs-id1169597569172"><problem id="fs-id1169597392586">
<para id="fs-id1169595251958">Find the intercepts of <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>6</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>.</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id1169595217650">
<title>Solution</title>
<para id="fs-id1169597618730">We will let <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> to find the <emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis>- intercept, and let <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> to find the <emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis>- intercept. We will fill in the table, which reminds us of what we need to find.</para>
