<para id="fs-id1169597577036">The steps to graph a linear equation using the intercepts are summarized below.</para>
<note id="fs-id1169597577088" class="howto">
<title>Graph a linear equation using the intercepts.</title>
<list id="fs-id1169597577094" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic" class="stepwise">
<item>Find the <emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis>- and <emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis>- intercepts of the line.
<list id="fs-id1169595223927" list-type="bulleted" bullet-style="open-circle">
<item>Let <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> and solve for <m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:math></item>
<item>Let <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> and solve for <m:math><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:math>.</item>
</list></item>
