<para id="fs-id1169597784798">This line has only one intercept. It is the point <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>.</para>
<para id="fs-id1169595313199">To ensure accuracy we need to plot three points. Since the <emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis>- and <emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis>- intercepts are the same point, we need <emphasis effect="italics">two</emphasis> more points to graph the line.</para>
