<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1169597836673">
<term>intercepts of a line</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1169597836678">The points where a line crosses the <emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis>- axis and the <emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis>- axis are called the intercepts of the line.</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1169597836693">
<term><emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis>- intercept</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1169597836702">The point <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mi>a</m:mi><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> where the line crosses the <emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis>- axis; the <emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis>- intercept occurs when <m:math><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:math> is zero.</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1169595259572">
<term><emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis>-intercept</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1169595259581">The point <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mi>b</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> where the line crosses the <emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis>- axis; the <emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis>- intercept occurs when <m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:math> is zero.</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
